x4freetext: A minimum systematic uncertainty of 10% was
assigned to all the measured differential inelastic
scattering values, as a conservative estimate of
uncertainties involved in the continuum subtraction
and summing procedures outlined in the article. At
large scattering angles and lower energies, the
experimental uncertainties can considerably exceed the
minimum systematic uncertainty. This increase arises
from counting statistics and assuming a minimum
uncertainty of 1.5 mb/sr due to unidentified causes,
as accepted for the elastic scattering measurements.
